    "attributes": {
        "action": "Treat Serious Youth Violence as a public health issue",
        "additional_details": "Adopting a public health approach to tackle SYV, particularly knife crime,  is essential.  It would focus on prevention, intervention, and support, addressing the social determinants contributing to the problem.  By treating SYV as a public health issue, we can work toward:\r\n\r\n\u2022\tEarly intervention\r\n\u2022\tCommunity-based solutions \r\n\u2022\tMental health and trauma support\r\n\u2022\tEducation and awareness\r\n\u2022\tResearch and data collection\r\n\u2022\tCollaboration\r\n\u2022\tThe creation of safer and healthier communities",
        "background": "The Government needs to treat Serious Youth Violence (SYV) as a pressing public health issue and take proactive measures to address its root causes.  SYV poses a significant threat to public safety, and it demands a comprehensive, multi-faceted approach that goes beyond law enforcement.",
